<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="512" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1436,1089,1474]" pageId="7" pageNumber="512">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1161,1186]" pageId="7" pageNumber="512">Remarks.</emphasis>
The genus 
<taxonomicName authority="Butler, 1877" authorityName="Butler" authorityYear="1877" box="[457,724,1161,1186]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Schasiura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="512" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[457,569,1161,1186]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="512">Schasiura</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Butler" box="[580,724,1161,1186]" pageId="7" pageNumber="512" refString="Butler, A. G. (1877) Illustrations of Typical Specimens of Lepidoptera Heterocera in the collection of the British Museum 1. Printed by the order of the Trustees of the British Museum, London, xiii + 62 pp, pls. 1 - 20." type="book chapter" year="1877">
Butler, 
<number box="[668,724,1162,1186]" pageId="7" pageNumber="512" value="1877.0">1877</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
includes two species, 
<taxonomicName box="[991,1172,1161,1186]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Schasiura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="512" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gymnelioides">
<emphasis box="[991,1172,1161,1186]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="512">S. gymnelioides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Butler, 1877" authorityName="Butler" authorityYear="1877" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Schasiura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="512" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mimica">
<emphasis box="[1234,1349,1162,1185]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="512">S. mimica</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Butler" pageId="7" pageNumber="512" refString="Butler, A. G. (1877) Illustrations of Typical Specimens of Lepidoptera Heterocera in the collection of the British Museum 1. Printed by the order of the Trustees of the British Museum, London, xiii + 62 pp, pls. 1 - 20." type="book chapter" year="1877">
Butler, 
<number box="[151,210,1198,1222]" pageId="7" pageNumber="512" value="1877.0">1877</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, the 
<typeStatus box="[269,317,1198,1222]" pageId="7" pageNumber="512">type</typeStatus>
species. There are no obvious characters uniting these two species that are not shared by many others currently classified in various genera (
<emphasis box="[652,936,1233,1258]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="512">
e.g., 
<taxonomicName authority="Draudt, 1917" authorityName="Draudt" authorityYear="1917" box="[706,936,1233,1258]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Osmocneme" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="512" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bracata">Osmocneme bracata</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
Draudt, 
<number box="[1035,1093,1234,1258]" pageId="7" pageNumber="512" value="1917.0">1917</number>
, 
<typeStatus box="[1104,1152,1234,1258]" pageId="7" pageNumber="512">type</typeStatus>
species of the monotypic genus 
<taxonomicName authority="Draudt, 1917" authorityName="Draudt" authorityYear="1917" box="[229,535,1269,1294]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Osmocneme" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="512" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[229,366,1270,1293]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="512">Osmocneme</emphasis>
Draudt, 
<number box="[476,535,1270,1294]" pageId="7" pageNumber="512" value="1917.0">1917</number>
</taxonomicName>
, and various species of 
<taxonomicName authority="Hubner, 1819" authorityName="Hubner" authorityYear="1819" box="[830,1136,1269,1294]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Autochloris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="512" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[830,961,1269,1294]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="512">Autochloris</emphasis>
Hübner, 
<number box="[1077,1136,1270,1294]" pageId="7" pageNumber="512" value="1819.0">1819</number>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Walker, 1854" authorityName="Walker" authorityYear="1854" box="[1152,1432,1269,1294]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Gymnelia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="512" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1152,1261,1269,1294]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="512">Gymnelia</emphasis>
Walker, 
<number box="[1373,1432,1269,1294]" pageId="7" pageNumber="512" value="1854.0">1854</number>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Felder, 1874" authorityName="Felder" authorityYear="1874" box="[151,447,1305,1330]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Dasysphinx" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="512" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,282,1305,1330]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="512">Dasysphinx</emphasis>
Felder, 
<number box="[388,447,1306,1330]" pageId="7" pageNumber="512" value="1874.0">1874</number>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName authority="Felder, 1874" authorityName="Felder" authorityYear="1874" box="[520,831,1305,1330]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Homoeocera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="512" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[520,665,1306,1329]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="512">Homoeocera</emphasis>
Felder, 
<number box="[771,831,1306,1330]" pageId="7" pageNumber="512" value="1874.0">1874</number>
</taxonomicName>
). A re-evaluation of the taxonomic position of 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Schasiura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="512" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gymnelioides">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="512">S. gymnelioides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
will require a comprehensive study of these and perhaps other related genera.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="512" type="reference_group">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1436,1089,1474]" pageId="7" pageNumber="512">
<taxonomicName box="[199,311,1377,1402]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Schasiura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="512" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[199,311,1377,1402]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="512">Schasiura</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was used by 
<bibRefCitation author="Hampson" box="[477,670,1378,1402]" pageId="7" pageNumber="512" refString="Hampson, G. F. (1914) Catalogue of the Lepidoptera Phalaenae in the British Museum, Supplement. vol. I. Catalogue of the Amatidae and Arctiadae (Nolinae and Lithosianae) in the collection of the British Museum. Printed by the order of the Trustees of the British Museum, London, 858 pp." type="book" year="1914">
Hampson (
<number box="[603,661,1378,1402]" pageId="7" pageNumber="512" value="1914.0">1914</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
as Hampson’s (
<number box="[860,918,1378,1402]" pageId="7" pageNumber="512" value="1898.0">1898</number>
) concept of 
<taxonomicName box="[1069,1200,1377,1402]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Autochloris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="512" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1069,1200,1377,1402]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="512">Autochloris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Julian P. Donahue, personal communication). Because 
<taxonomicName box="[572,703,1413,1438]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Autochloris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="512" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[572,703,1413,1438]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="512">Autochloris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was placed in 
<taxonomicName box="[898,1043,1413,1438]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="512" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subTribe" subTribe="Euchromiina">Euchromiina</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Forbes" box="[1099,1267,1413,1438]" pageId="7" pageNumber="512" refString="Forbes, W. T. M. (1939) The Lepidoptera of Barro Colorado Island, Panama. Bulletin of the Museum of Comparative Zoology, 85 (4), 97 - 322." type="journal article" year="1939">
Forbes (
<number box="[1198,1258,1414,1438]" pageId="7" pageNumber="512" value="1939.0">1939</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
, we kept this subtribal assignment.
</paragraph>
